    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-13T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-13T09:00:00-05:00" n="413"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d413">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/250: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at São Paulo</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CCR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cameron</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">São Paulo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-13T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >July 13, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 13—10:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Notice regarding deposition President of Minas Geraes not confirmed but neither
                    Federal nor Minas Geraes State troops near border have up to the present time
                    moved against São Paulo. Vanguard São Paulo troops now at Bianor, State of Rio
                    de Janeiro. <persName corresp="#p_KGB1">General Klinger</persName> made supreme
                    military chief of movement and has been appointed Governor of Matto Grosso with
                    headquarters at Campo Grande. Santos reported blockaded by destroyer and
                    hydroplanes. São Paulo absolutely united and hoping for favorable <hi
                        rend="italic">coup d’état</hi> in Rio de Janeiro at any time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cameron</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
